<br>
Best combination is a rogue with sneak and a ranger binding sight on the rogue. In Sons case you just need a nonKoS person as the bind target.<br>
<br>
You can also do a similar trick with bards in some places and bind sight You can jump across mobs by using their sight through entire dungeons to get to a specific target you want targetted. Bards bind sight last longer and is more efficient for these most things. It lasts until they run out of stamina and a good bard can twist stamina right along with it.<br>
<br>
It was one way people used to pull Phini to zone in Kedge. Bind sight has been nerfed since so there is a lot of things you cant do like this anymore though.<br>
<br>
So be surprised :) <p><p align=left><font face="Trebuchet MS, Tahoma" size="1"><a href=http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=6031>Ligge</a> - Changing Tide CoGuildleader<br><font color=green><a href="http://pub17.ezboard.com/beqguide">Changing Tide's Boards</a><b> || </b><a href="http://pub2.ezboard.com/bthefolk">The Folk's Boards</a></font><br><img src=http://www.eqguide.com/changingtide/images/inpom.jpg><br><b>"You must be the change you wish to see in the world." - Mahatma Ghandi</b><br>"Never argue with an idiot. They drag you down to their level then beat you with experience."</font></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utils.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tils</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.gifs.net/animate/worm.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(9/12/01 7:30:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=131.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.datacruz.com/~game/tils.jpg height=184 width=125></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sontalak + Harmony question</span><hr size=1> Harmony trick used to work for kos people....they nerfed it about 2 patches ago...now you cant get close enough to cast before he agros.<br>
